      </sec>
      <sec id="SEC3-1-3">
        <label>C.</label>
        <title>Detection of TIS</title>
        <p>This module uses as input TIS-Ribo-Seq data. To block the ribosomal transition from initiation into elongation and to detect bona fide initiating ribosomes in prokaryotes, several antibiotics have been used so far, e.g. retapamulin (<xref rid="B19" ref-type="bibr">19</xref>), Onc112 (<xref rid="B22" ref-type="bibr">22</xref>), tetracycline (<xref rid="B33" ref-type="bibr">33</xref>). Thereby, retapamulin shows the sharpest peak at initiation. Considering the middle nucleotide of each TIS-Seq read and summing up TIS counts at the start codon including one codon upstream and downstream (<xref rid="sup1" ref-type="supplementary-material">Supplementary Figure S2</xref>), smORFer selects smORFs with ≥5 RPFs at TIS (the same cutoff as for <italic toggle="yes">translated</italic> above) and categorizes them as <italic toggle="yes">translated</italic> with TIS signal (Figure <xref rid="F1" ref-type="fig">1</xref>, Table <xref rid="tbl1" ref-type="table">1</xref>).</p>
